{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"rationale\":\"Bead meets 7 of 8 rubric criteria. Title is imperative and names the subsystem. Description has all four required sections: PROBLEM, ROOT CAUSE with four explicit file:line anchors (FEAT-004:39-41, FEAT-008:223-229, FEAT-008:243-263, FEAT-010:343-352, ADR-024:156-170), PROPOSED FIX, and NON-SCOPE. AC is numbered with 6 verifiable items. Labels carry phase:2, area:*, kind:doc, and three spec cross-refs plus adr:024. Parent and deps are explicit ('No deps'). No /tmp references or chat dependencies. Doc-only waivers applied for the missing go test gate and Test* AC reference. Single deduction: self-test criterion fails — 6 consecutive execution attempts (2 BLOCK + 4 no_changes_unjustified) demonstrate that an agent given only this bead body cannot complete the task. The AC items describe which documents to amend at a high level ('adds user stories for…', 'specifies terminal review…') but provide no prescriptive content guidance — no schema fragments, no example table rows, no state-machine entries — leaving the executing agent without enough signal to actually write the required spec text. Repeated harness routing failures (missing-harness lint warning on every attempt) are a secondary executability signal.\",\"score\":7,\"suggested_fixes\":[\"Add a harness field (e.g., harness: claude) to resolve the repeated missing-harness lint warnings that fire on every execute-bead invocation.\",\"Expand each AC item with prescriptive content: specify the exact table rows, state-machine transitions, or schema keys to add — e.g., 'FEAT-004 adds a Needs-human lane table with columns: trigger condition, metadata keys set, worker-skip rule, ready/status count impact' — so the agent knows what to write, not just which file to touch.\",\"Add an inline sketch of the expected spec output (a short markdown excerpt or a representative table row) directly in the Description PROPOSED FIX section; the six execution failures indicate agents cannot infer the required structure from the current prose alone.\",\"Replace the current AC 6 with two separate lines: 'cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./... green (no Go source changes; smoke-only)' and 'lefthook run pre-commit passes', matching the rubric's required gate order.\"],\"waivers_applied\":[\"doc-only-no-go-test-gate: bead is area:docs kind:doc with no Go source changes; the 'cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./\\u003cpaths\\u003e/... green' AC gate is not applicable and deduction is waived.\",\"doc-only-no-test-function: bead is area:docs kind:doc; no Test* function or go test -run filter exists to reference in AC; deduction is waived.\"]}","created_at":"2026-05-07T04:12:28.506158953Z","kind":"bead-quality.lint","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"score=7"}
